The paper deals with the problem of publishing location datasets in a differentially private manner, which is a topic related to data privacy and security. This suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DB (Databases) or cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a mechanism based on isotonic regression, which is a statistical method for preserving the order of data points, and employs locality preserving functions to map the dataset to a bounded interval, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed mechanism and its ability to answer other queries accurately, which suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category.
